From: rtp-llm <noreply@alibaba-inc.com>
Date: Sat, 26 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] cuda13 compat: fully initialize PyModuleDef

The FLASHINFER_EXT_MODULE_INIT macro in csrc/pytorch_extension_utils.h
populates only the first 5 fields of PyModuleDef and relies on the rest
being zero-initialized.  GCC's -Wmissing-field-initializers (promoted to
error under -Werror in this build) flags the trailing m_slots /
m_traverse / m_clear / m_free members; extend the initializer list so
the header compiles cleanly in the CUDA 13 ARM build environment.

--- csrc/pytorch_extension_utils.h
+++ csrc/pytorch_extension_utils.h
@@ -50,6 +50,10 @@
       -1,     /* size of per-interpreter state of the module, \
                  or -1 if the module keeps state in global variables. */ \
       NULL,   /* methods */ \
+      NULL,   /* m_slots */ \
+      NULL,   /* m_traverse */ \
+      NULL,   /* m_clear */ \
+      NULL,   /* m_free */ \
     }; \
     return PyModule_Create(&module_def); \
   } \
